{
  "stem": "22237.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's a small synagogue where mostly people prayed that came from Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They spoke-- amongst themselves, they always spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we also went along with them to that synagogue.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But as we got older, we would go to the more modern synagogues.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Frankfurt had many modern synagogues.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there was especially one that was called the Borneplatz Synagogue, that I mentioned before already.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So the-- the children, we, many times, went to-- most of the time, we went to these modern synagogues, mostly this Borneplatz Synagogue.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There was also another synagogue called Breuer, B-R-E-- B-R-E-U-E-R.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that was a more orthodox synagogue.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We were not-- we were orthodox, but not Hasidic orthodox, what we would call today Hasidic.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we children kind of went back and forth.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We would go to the big synagogue, go back to the [INAUDIBLE] that my parents used to called it, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Visited our parents and tell them where we are and then walk out again and go to the other synagogue.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that was our way of life on-- on Saturdays and holidays, Jewish holidays.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Would you spell Borneplatz for us?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, it's B-O-R-N-E-P-L-A-T-Z synagogue.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the Borneplatz synagogue was visited mostly by Germans, not the ones who originated in Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They would speak German in that synagogue, while the [INAUDIBLE] [LAUGHS] would-- people would speak Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As we grew up in Germany, we children would be more-- would-- liked better to be amongst people that were Germans, because that was where we were-- where we grew up.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "While my parents enjoyed rather being amongst people that they knew from Poland or that spoke their language.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We understood Yiddish when they spoke to us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we children, growing up in Germany, spoke German.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We would call it Hochdeutsche in German.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
